Round 2 of Phase 7 surface migration. Three regions ported per the
Phase 7.1 StatusBar recipe, bundled into a single chromium patch
because every region mutates the same shared files (BUILD.gn,
webui_url_constants, SlayzoneBrowserView, slayzone_region_container,
slayzone_webui_registry, chrome_browser_interface_binders_*).

NEW: chrome/browser/ui/webui/slayzone/slayzone_webui_bundle_source.{h,cc}
recipe-refinement #1 approved by orchestrator after Round 1. Extracts
the ~100-LoC-per-region bundle-serving + CSP + missing-bundle-fallback
pattern into a single slayzone::ConfigureBundleSource helper. Regions
now call:

    auto* source = content::WebUIDataSource::CreateAndAdd(...);
    slayzone::ConfigureBundleSource(source, "<region>",
                                     kRegionMissingBundleHtml);

and get: --slayzone-webui-bundle-dir/<region>/dist/<path> file-read on
a MayBlock worker, plus the standard SlayZone CSP (script-src 'self'
chrome://resources, style/font/img 'self' data:/inline, TrustedTypes
disabled). 7.4/7.5/7.6 all use the helper; 7.1/7.2/7.3/7.9 will
migrate opportunistically in a later rebase. Statusbar keeps its
inline copy for now so the 7.1 reference implementation stays
self-contained.

Per-region surface:

**7.4 tasklist** — kanban board. Minimal spike surface: TasklistColumn
list with TaskEntry rows (id + title + status). Full drag-drop + card
chrome lands when parity harness flags the gap. tasklist:get-snapshot
forwards via SlayzoneTasklistHost. Region already had a WebView slot
in SlayzoneSplitView (Phase 5.4); 7.4 only flips its URL from
placeholder to chrome://slayzone-tasklist/.

**7.5 sidebar** — task-metadata side panel. description + tags
(SidebarTag list) + priority (0-3). chrome://slayzone-sidebar/ +
SlayzoneSidebarHost. sidebar:get-snapshot forwards to sidecar.

**7.6 taskheader** — task title row. title + status + statusOptions
list. chrome://slayzone-taskheader/ + SlayzoneTaskheaderHost.
taskheader:get-snapshot forwards to sidecar.

Shared file deltas: each region adds a URL host + ChromeURLHosts entry
+ WebUIConfig registration + ForWebUI<>.Add<>() binder + mojom() input
+ SlayzoneBrowserView unique_ptr member + accessor + RegionUrl
conditional. Mechanical; matches R1 shape verbatim.

